<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Yes the New Testament evolved, and before any writing became Scripture it was tested and approved by usage. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
We seem to have a disagreement on the meaning of &quot;Scripture&quot;.  I believe it is inherently authoritative, and was invested with such authority as the ink dried on the page.<br>
<br>
Church councils simply recognized what was already witnessed by the Spirit.  And so, the fact that an early church father is a witness to canonicity does not render his interpretations binding.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>2 Peter 3:15-16 (NIV)<br>
