<br>
To me this doesn't sound all that different from some Christains who firmly believe in the Genesis account including the chronological time line making the earth a few thousand years old.  Even though everything scientifically points to the earth being millions of years old, many say it's only thousands because &quot;God made it so&quot;.<br>
<br>
Scientifically analyze or taste the communion elements and you will surely come out with bread and wine.  However, many beleive that is really IS the body and blood of Christ, simply because &quot;God made it so&quot;.  And like the Genesis account, if scripture (John 6) is taken literally, it fits. <p>Christians know that it is not possible to reject or ignore God without demeaning man<br>
- John Paul II at WYD 2002<br>
